compute_percentages <- function(column) {
  # Ensure the factor levels are set to 1, 2, and 3
  column <- factor(column, levels=c(1, 2, 3))
  
  # Create a dataframe with the two relevant columns
  df <- data.frame(site2 = owi150$site2, column = column)
  
  # Filter out rows where either column has NA
  filtered_data <- df[complete.cases(df), ]
  
  counts <- table(filtered_data$site2, filtered_data$column)
  percentages <- prop.table(counts, margin=1) * 100
  
  return(t(percentages))
}
arcsine_transform <- function(x) {
  asin(sqrt(x / 100))  # Transform percentage to proportion and apply arcsine
}

owi300_categorized <- owi300 %>%
  mutate(Wr_category = case_when(
    Wr_wild > 90 ~ ">90",
    Wr_wild >= 75 & Wr_wild <= 90 ~ "75-90",
    Wr_wild < 75 ~ "<75"
  )) %>%
  group_by(site2, Wr_category) %>%
  summarise(Count = n(), .groups = 'drop')

# Step 2 & 3: Calculate the total counts for normalization and percentage for each category
owi300_percentage <- owi300_categorized %>%
  group_by(site2) %>%
  mutate(TotalCount = sum(Count)) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  mutate(Percentage = (Count / TotalCount) * 100)
print(owi300_percentage)

compute_percentages <- function(column) {
  # Ensure the factor levels are set to 1, 2, and 3
  column <- factor(column, levels=c(0, 1, 2, 3))
  
  # Create a dataframe with the two relevant columns
  df <- data.frame(site2 = histo150$site2, column = column)
  
  # Filter out rows where either column has NA
  filtered_data <- df[complete.cases(df), ]
  
  counts <- table(filtered_data$site2, filtered_data$column)
  percentages <- prop.table(counts, margin=1) * 100
  
  return(t(percentages))
}
# Compute the percentages for histo parameters
infla_percentages <- compute_percentages(histo150$Inflammation)
fibro_percentages <- compute_percentages(histo150$Fibrosis)
cong_percentages <- compute_percentages(histo150$Congestion)
necr_percentages <- compute_percentages(histo150$Necrosis)
# Combine vertically
all_percentages <- cbind(cong_percentages, infla_percentages, necr_percentages, fibro_percentages)
